Opisthobranchia von Santa Marta, ColombiaSummary The classification of a collection of opisthobranchs from Santa Marta, Colombia, resulted in 36 species, two of which, Chromodoris perola and Calmella bandeli, are new to Science. For comparison a specimen of Chromodoris clenchi from Puerto was studied. The disjunctive characters of some species of Aplysia are discussed.